## Material Selection

The final design uses Aluminum 7475-T7651 due to its balance of ductility, strength, and fracture toughness.

- Young’s Modulus: 10 × 10⁶ psi  
- Poisson Ratio: 0.29  
- Ultimate Strength: ~65 ksi  
- Fracture Toughness (K<sub>IC</sub>): ~46 ksi√in  

This alloy supports the higher strain concentration at the reduced section while maintaining structural reliability.

---

## Finite Element Analysis (ANSYS)

### Boundary Conditions

- Drive end constrained along upper 0.40 in  
- Applied torque of 600 in·lbf at the handle  

