## Sensitivity Prediction (mV/V)

A half-bridge Wheatstone configuration predicts output using:

<div style="background:#f6f8fa; padding:12px; border-radius:6px;">
V<sub>out</sub> / V<sub>in</sub> ≈ (Gauge Factor × 2 × Strain) / 4  
</div>

With gauge factor 2.05 and strain of 1.055 × 10⁻³:

**Predicted Sensitivity:** ≥ 1.0 mV/V at 600 in·lbf  

This exceeds the required minimum and more than doubles the baseline output.

---

## Strain Gauge Selection

**Gauge Model:** Vishay EA-06-125BZ-350  
**Type:** 350 Ω linear foil strain gauge  

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Gauge Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Grid Length</td><td>3.18 mm</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Grid Width</td><td>1.57 mm</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Pattern Type</td><td>Linear</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

The selected gauge matches the reduced-section footprint and the predicted strain distribution.

---

## Conclusion

The final torque wrench design:

- Meets all structural, fatigue, and fracture requirements  
- Achieves over double the baseline strain-gauge sensitivity  
- Provides clean strain fields appropriate for half-bridge measurement  
- Demonstrates a full analytical-to-FEM engineering workflow  

The improved geometry validates the wrench as an improved instrumented system for torque measurement.
